      <text>My thoughts - don't screw up stuff. It's mostly that simple. We're not
Tyme, we're not any of those others, we are us. One draw to anything is
that you find the point of heightened activity, conflict, or interest
and you market that. Confining the Rebels to their camp or to Salidar
is pretty much a bad idea. Merging the towers is even worse. You want
conflict. People scream they want treaties and they want this and that
but if this were a peaceful place, why would we even sign in? The most
difficult thing to do is progress to a point where it becomes unknown
territory or there is no story. The appeal of Fang has been that it is the
WoT.. we haven't made it what we wanted, we kept it like it was.. the
books. So pushing people off into something that sounds good in theory,
is often a bad idea in outcome. Not to mention, you have every situation
to consider, the personal roleplay, what it will do, what it won't do,
how to correct the possible problems (and you won't see them all), not
to mention, coordinating it all. Looks easy. Is it? *shake*

&amp;r-&amp;wDanielle&amp;n

It really isn't that difficult to find RP and RP usually does not depend
upon what Rand al'Thor is doing. 99% of us wouldn't even be involved ICly.
