      <text>If you read 'handbook' it gives job descriptions. I'm going to post that
here. Some things I want to stress.

Guildleader: Your job is simply to run your Guild. You must play at least 
10 hours a week. The guild is yours. You decide what the ranks and help 
files are, and what your guildeq looks like. The guild zone is yours as 
well, but any changes must be okayed by the Headbuilder. You must have no 
less than 4 eq for every single rank in your guild. You should try to have 
regular guild meetings. You should run guild quests, with the same rules 
applying as normal quests (see Quest Policy) . You should promote roleplay 
and try to make your guild ICly respectable. You will not try to have the 
strongest eq or skills. All new skills must be agreed upon by the Creator 
and Weaver imms. Your only focus is your guild, nothing more. Only you can 
make the guild fun, full of people and a presence in the mud.

Now, first point - &quot;You must play at least 10 hours a week.&quot;  This is
because you are needed. I expect this to be followed. I know life happens
and I'm willing to work with people that need it, but otherwise, I want
you here and active. For those not making 10 hours or it's been a while
since they've logged in, I'm mailing with a time period. No response, no
imm.

Second - &quot;You should promote roleplay and try to make your guild ICly
respectable.&quot; We all want to be respected and we don't want our guildies
to face snickering, right? .. promoting roleplay .. Promote. Period.

As always, if you have questions or issues with this, talk to me.

&amp;r-&amp;wAmarinda&amp;n
