&amp;c*************************************************************************&amp;n
&amp;C6.&amp;w  All players have the right to privacy. An Immortal may not snoop or
    sit in rooms invisible simply for recreation without a GOOD reason(s)
    and only after announcing it to the appropriate person/people.
    -
    Snnoping should be used only if concerned a player is cheating, to
    watch code troubles, or to evaluate roleplay.
    -
    If you're watching roleplay or checking bugs, ask the player before
    snooping. If you're snooping because you suspect he/she's cheating,
    inform either an admin IMM or announce it via wiznet and discuss it
    with other IMMs first.
&amp;c*************************************************************************&amp;n
&amp;C7.  &amp;wDon't harass morts for amusement. Don't set their titles, force
    them to say things, pkill them, spam them with socials or sends, or
    load aggressive mobs to their rooms.
&amp;c*************************************************************************&amp;n
&amp;C10. &amp;wDo not stat eq or mobs or players and give out that info to the
    players, including your own alts (that is, don't stat for stats).
    There is a reason are commands like consider, test, and appraise. Do
    not give info about one player to another, such as if he/she is a DF.
&amp;WI will go as far as to include telling someone who a player's alt would be.
&amp;c*************************************************************************
&amp;C11. &amp;wTransfer and teleport are reserved for OOC reasons when you need a
    player to be in your room to chat with, or are running a quest or a
    guild event. Do not use them to help players get to roleplay sites,
    to go find eq, or kill mobs. We have very extensive travelling commands
    (cart, gate, skim, guildwalk, speedwalk, run, seek, recall, etc.) for
    this purpose.
&amp;WThis includes your own alts.&amp;n
&amp;c*************************************************************************
&amp;C16. &amp;wUse gecho, at &lt;command&gt;, send, page, and other such commands
    sparingly. We are not here to spam each other and the players.
&amp;WGLs would be helped by using gecho for guild advertisements, but keep
all gechoes to a minimum. Morts don't have a choice in seeing these as well
as the other commands mentioned.
&amp;c*************************************************************************
&amp;C18. &amp;wIssues discussed exculsively with immortals should remain at that
    level. It is strictly prohibited to copy/paste wiznet to mortals and
    copy/paste posts from IMM boards to mortals. This is a cause for
    deIMMing. Mortals should -never- hear about IMM business. Mortals are
    here to play the game, not to get involved in admin/IMM issues. Do
    not tell mortals about IMM politics, admin issues, or any Imm business.
