a little while now. So, here's the post to clear up any/all problems.

I'm addressing GLs with this because there are specifics that you should
be aware of and things that you must think about. Nobility titles are
only allowed on the bookie imms that have an IC presence and that have
earned the nobility title. This means that Prophet, M'Hael, and General
are allowed because they are bookies and are around IC. Those that are
not bookies will not have nobility titles. This is a tool for the Houses
GL and the SC GL, but only them, and only for the mort players. It is
not to be abused, not to be set for good time's sake, and not to make
a statement. True, this applies to all imms due to the problems in the
past, but since we do have bookies that are GLs, you should be aware of
the stipulation that alters this slightly.

If you have questions, please talk to me. I don't intend on making any
GLs bookies during my time of hiring GLs. It's worked before and I don't
have a problem with those that are currently around AS LONG as those
bookies are played.

