      <authorname>Tzeentch</authorname>
      <text>
We have a spiffy bit of new code to play with. It's called dynvars. I 
think that stands for dynamically variable descriptions... anyway, what it
does is allows us to vary descriptions based on time of day, type of
weather, or abilities of the person who is looking. It can be applied to
rooms, mobs or objects and to the exdescs on them, as well. Stefan has
provided a tutorial (and a better explanation) along with some examples at

http://www.dragonsfang.org/coder/embed/

Check it out. This is a neat little thing that allows us to add extra bits
of description that someone will see if he is wolfkin or grasping the
source or if it is daytime or whatnot. If you have any questions, ask Stefan
or me and we'll be glad to try to answer.

-Tze
</text>
