      <text>I don't think it's very feasible for joe randlander to have a large wild animal as a pet.  First of all, they are called &quot;large wild animals.&quot;  Note the word &quot;wild,&quot; which the Mirriam-Webster dictionary defines as, &quot;Living in a state of nature and not ordinarily tamed or domesticated.&quot;  Secondly, it must be pointed out that the average character on this mud doesn't really have the background knowledge necessary to successfully domesticate a large wild animal.  Writing a background and then adding, &quot;Oh, and I also studied with the circus for three years just before joining the &lt;guildname&gt;, so I know how to train bears&quot; seems like bullshit to me.
That said, if a player wants to dedicate a significant amount of his character's life to the training and research required to tame a large wild animal, the possibility should at least be considered before being denied.  So I guess my vote is to look at everyone on a case-by-case thing.
-Teak
</text>
